<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="B" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Bankrupt1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Bankrupt</orth> (O. Edd. often <emph>bankrout</emph>), adj., insolvent; <cit><quote>they prove b. in this poor-rich gain,</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 140" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 140</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>a. b. beggar,</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 140" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 140</bibl></cit> <bibl n="shak. son 67.9" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 67, 9</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 2.4.42" default="NO" valid="yes">Gentl. II, 4, 42</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 1.1.27" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL I, 1, 27</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 3.2.85" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. III, 2, 85</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 2.1.151" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 II, 1, 151</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 2.1.151" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 II, 1, 151</bibl> <bibl n="shak. h5 4.2.43" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 IV, 2, 43</bibl>. Followed by <emph>of</emph>: <cit><quote>what a face I have, since it is b. of his majesty,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r2 4.267" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 IV, 267</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>